disproportionately impacted communities, with an emphasis on rural
areas, communities of color, and low-income populations. The advisory
guidance must include strategies, within the provider's scope of practice,
for maintaining access to immunizations, cancer screenings, and family
planning services for these communities.
1 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Colorado:
2 SECTION 1. Legislative declaration - legislative intent.
3 (1) The general assembly finds and declares that:
4 (a) Reductions or changes in federal health-care funding
5 associated with the federal budget bill, H.R. 1 of the 119th Congress
6 (2025-2026), Pub.L. 119-21, including the bill's ban on spending
7 medicaid dollars on services provided by essential community providers,
8 have the potential to disproportionately harm disproportionately impacted
9 communities;
10 (b) These impacts may result in loss of coverage, reduced access
11 to care, worsened health outcomes, and a strain on community health
12 systems; and
13 (c) The state of Colorado must safeguard disproportionately
14 impacted communities.
15 (2) It is the intent of the general assembly that the department of
16 public health and environment and the department of health care policy
17 and financing carry out the requirements of this act through the use of
18 existing resources.
